&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and implement software on ECUs running Linux&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help architect interfaces between various networking components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help define and implement safety and security requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support hardware engineers with PCB bring up, debugging and testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Model exemplary software development practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-10 years of experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of C and C++&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Linux kernel and drivers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of at least one embedded Linux distribution (i.e. Yocto or Buildroot)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of Ethernet, IP, and higher levels of networking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hardware-based ethernet packet processors (VLANs, Filtering engines, TCAMs, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity with features of at least one network switching ASICs is a must (Broadcom, Marvell, or Microchip switches preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of electrical engineering fundamentals to support low level debugging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
