&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;Aurora’s mission is to deliver the benefits of self-driving technology safely, quickly, and broadly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;https://aurora.tech/aurora-driver&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://aurora.tech/aurora-driver&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;The Aurora Driver&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;will create a new era in mobility and logistics, one that will bring a safer, more efficient, and more accessible future to everyone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;At Aurora, you will tackle massively complex problems alongside other passionate, intelligent individuals, growing as an expert while expanding your knowledge. For the latest news from Aurora, visit&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://aurora.tech/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;aurora.tech&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or follow us on&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/company/auroradriver&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aurora hires talented people with diverse backgrounds who are ready to help build a transportation ecosystem that will make our roads safer, get crucial goods where they need to go, and make mobility more efficient and accessible for all. We are searching for a Staff Network Planning and Logistics Analyst to join the Operations Strategy team, who would be based in Dallas, TX.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will lead the planning and analysis of our logistics network, resource allocation, and load scheduling strategies to optimize efficiency and profitability. You’ll serve as a key thought partner to cross-functional stakeholders, helping translate operational challenges into scalable, data-informed solutions.This role requires strong analytical skills combined with business acumen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Product, Business Development, &amp;amp; Dispatch stakeholders to develop plans and drive day-to-day optimization of our network of resources (people, trucks, terminals) against demand (commercial and development)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage Lean Six Sigma principles and data analysis to identify and recommend opportunities to reduce waste and drive efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define business needs and partner with Product and Engineering to develop requirements for fleet allocation, load management, and network optimization tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply logistics engineering principles to support the design and continuous improvement of terminal layouts, routing logic, and resource flow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create weekly resource allocation schedules based on inputs &amp;amp; outputs of fleet allocation, load management, and network optimization tools&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build forecasting models and apply industrial engineering methods (e.g., layout optimization, time studies) to improve terminal throughput and fleet efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance and Strategy teams to evaluate cost trade-offs and support revenue growth planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of the needs and constraints of our logistics partners to enhance service delivery and cost-effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize data analytics to track performance metrics, monitor performance against targets, and identify areas of inefficiencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and synthesize data-driven reports and executive-ready insights on current and projected resource utilization and alignment to revenue growth plans while proactively identifying &amp;amp; mitigating potential constraints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS in a quantitative field or engineering field (e.g. Industrial Engineering, Economics, Math, Statistics, Finance)&lt;/li&gt;
