&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;At Aurora, you will tackle massively complex problems alongside other passionate, intelligent individuals, growing as an expert while expanding your knowledge. For the latest news from Aurora, visit&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://aurora.tech/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;aurora.tech&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or follow us on&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/company/auroradriver&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Aurora hires talented people with diverse backgrounds who are ready to help build a transportation ecosystem that will make our roads safer, get crucial goods where they need to go, and make mobility more efficient and accessible for all. &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re searching for a &lt;/span&gt;Staff Photonics Engineer&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design passive and active photonic devices using advanced modeling and simulation tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate schematic designs into physical layouts through Python-based layout scripting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with foundries to ensure process compatibility and facilitate successful tapeouts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and interpret metrologies to validate process integrity and correlate with PIC performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement wafer-level and die-level test plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support cross-functional product teams in integrating PICs into larger modules or subsystems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master / Ph.D. degree in physics, electrical, or computer engineering or relevant fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of research or industrial experience with integrated photonics chip design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fundamental understanding of electronics, optics and integrated photonics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High proficiency in Python or similar object-oriented programming languages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with III-V active photonics design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with radar, lidar or other optical sensing systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with integrated photonics chips or systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with photonic hybrid integration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The base salary range for this position is $181,000 - $290,000 per year. Aurora’s pay ranges are determined by role, level, and location. Within the range, the successful candidate’s starting base pay will be determined based on factors including job-related skills, experience, qualifications, relevant education or training, and market conditions. These ranges may be modified in the future. The successful candidate will also be eligible for an annual bonus, equity compensation, and benefits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
