&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Flexport:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Flexport, we believe global trade can move the human race forward. That’s why it’s our mission to make global commerce so easy there will be more of it. We’re shaping the future of a $10T industry with solutions powered by innovative technology and exceptional people. Today, companies of all sizes—from emerging brands to Fortune 500s—use Flexport technology to move more than $19B of merchandise across 112 countries a year.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The recent global supply chain crisis has put Flexport center stage as we continue to play a pivotal role in how goods move around the world. We are proud to have the support of the best investors in the game who believe in our mission, solutions and people. Ready to tackle global challenges that impact business, society, and the environment? Come join us.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build elegant solutions to complex supply chain problems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The opportunity:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexport’s Fulfillment team ensures that our merchants can scale efficiently while we design smarter ways to store and move goods across the country. As a Demand Planner, you’ll lead critical forecasting, capacity, and planning initiatives that enable the reliability and scalability of our fulfillment network. You’ll collaborate closely with Sales, Operations, Finance, and Product to align demand with operations, anticipate constraints, and design proactive solutions. Our team thrives on solving complex logistics challenges, and we are looking for a strategic, analytical leader to help us continue pushing the boundaries of efficiency and customer experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, calibrate, and maintain forecasting models across all fulfillment services&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the long-term fulfillment network plan and financial forecast to balance supply, demand, and capacity needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct root cause analysis of volume deviations and partner with Operations to identify opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop scenario plans for changes to operating cost and contracts, demand uncertainty, capacity constraints, and transportation lanes to optimize our fulfillment strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional S&amp;amp;OP discussions with senior leadership to align business plans and future investment with fulfillment network capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner directly with our merchants to solve challenges and proactively find opportunities to improve cost, service, and support the growth of their business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Supply Chain, Operations, Engineering, Analytics, Business, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in supply chain management, forecasting, demand planning, or fulfillment operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency in Google Sheets or Excel; strong SQL for data extraction/analysis; familiarity with BI/visualization tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills, with the ability to drive decision-making across functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;A &quot;compliance first&quot; attitude to keep our regulators happy and enthusiastic about Flexport since we operate in a heavily regulated industry.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
