&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Flexport:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Flexport, we believe global trade can move the human race forward. That’s why it’s our mission to make global commerce so easy there will be more of it. We’re shaping the future of a $10T industry with solutions powered by innovative technology and exceptional people. Today, companies of all sizes—from emerging brands to Fortune 500s—use Flexport technology to move more than $19B of merchandise across 112 countries a year.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The recent global supply chain crisis has put Flexport center stage as we continue to play a pivotal role in how goods move around the world. We are proud to have the support of the best investors in the game who believe in our mission, solutions and people. Ready to tackle global challenges that impact business, society, and the environment? Come join us.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support the operational excellence that drives our business forward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an experienced, sharp, and highly trustworthy Executive Assistant in direct support of our Chief Financial Officer. You’ll work alongside leaders to maximize their ability to focus on the team’s key priorities in supporting Flexport’s continued growth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who thrives in a fast-moving, ambiguous environment, and who brings a calm, strategic presence to dynamic executive offices. You will act as a force multiplier, managing day-to-day operations, enabling strategic alignment, and strengthening communication across the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Role responsibilities include managing multiple complex calendars, planning and organizing events of all sizes, and coordinating domestic and international travel. This candidate will help build a positive team environment and establish working relationships inside and outside of the group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a strategic partner to your assigned executive (CFO) by managing schedules, priorities, and key communications with precision and foresight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate cross-functional interactions with senior leaders, external partners, board members, and other key stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate needs, problem-solve on the fly, and help your executive stay ahead of their most critical workstreams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and drive logistics for high-impact initiatives, travel, meetings, and events (e.g., QBRs, offsites, internal communications).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle confidential and non-routine matters with discretion, judgment, and professionalism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and organize data and reports, identifying insights or solutions when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support heavy calendar management, domestic/international travel, expenses, POs, and other administrative tasks with speed and accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build trusted relationships with internal stakeholders, including the broader C-Suite and their EAs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A BA/BS degree and 3-5+ years of experience supporting senior executives in fast-paced, high-growth environments (tech or start-up experience preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Impeccable communication skills — concise, clear, and thoughtful, with strong writing ability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of handling sensitive matters and navigating complex dynamics with diplomacy and sound judgment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong emotional intelligence, with the ability to anticipate needs, resolve issues proactively, and foster a culture of trust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A bias for action — you operate with urgency, adapt quickly, and keep momentum high even when the path isn’t perfectly clear.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep commitment to Flexport’s values and mission, with a genuine interest in business, culture, and making organizations better from the inside out.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;c-message_kit__gutter&quot;&gt;
