&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Flexport:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Flexport, we believe global trade can move the human race forward. That’s why it’s our mission to make global commerce so easy there will be more of it. We’re shaping the future of a $10T industry with solutions powered by innovative technology and exceptional people. Today, companies of all sizes—from emerging brands to Fortune 500s—use Flexport technology to move more than $19B of merchandise across 112 countries a year.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The recent global supply chain crisis has put Flexport center stage as we continue to play a pivotal role in how goods move around the world. We are proud to have the support of the best investors in the game who believe in our mission, solutions and people. Ready to tackle global challenges that impact business, society, and the environment? Come join us.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support and delight Flexport’s clients&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexport is looking for a partnership driven, commercially minded individual to own regional leadership of trucking/vendor strategy and execution within the Benelux and France. You will not only manage partnerships and drive carrier development, but also help promote net revenue growth by means of strategic procurement, volume allocation and pricing decisions for your region.&amp;nbsp; This role enables you to work cross-functionally among several different teams at Flexport, such as the Client Solutions, Network and Trade Lade Management operations, Ocean, Finance and Legal.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for bringing on new business, growing existing accounts, driving technology adoption, overseeing service compliance and much more.&amp;nbsp; You will organize the development of new services and lanes within your markets to ensure Flexport upholds the strongest carrier network in the industry. This role allows you to become an expert in your domain while exposing you to multiple facets of the Freight Forwarding business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execute on regional trucking strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; ensure healthy growth within their markets, execute carrier and market strategy, negotiate carrier contracts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop and manage local carrier partnerships:&lt;/strong&gt; maintain, manage, and be key growth contact for trucking partner relationships with your market. Ensuring success of&amp;nbsp; technology strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage trucking partner SLAs: &lt;/strong&gt;including compliance in relation to performance, compliance and technology use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Procure and negotiate rates for your markets:&lt;/strong&gt; maintain competitive spot and contract rates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own pricing strategy and drive net revenue within your local markets&lt;/strong&gt;: provide markup and ICC guidance, set sell tariffs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establish regular market updates as the regional trucking expert&lt;/strong&gt;: leading enablement with an in depth understanding of the local market nuances and conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client solutions &amp;amp; account support&lt;/strong&gt;: support sales in winning new business, including attending and joining client meetings.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA/BS degree and 2+/or 4+ years of experience in relevant freight forwarding, transportation or supply chain roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of product and technology within the industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and network with regards to trucking/service procurement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building and maintaining relationships and partnerships with vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical skills and metric / data based approach to solving problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical background and knowledge of analytical tools (Excel, etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic vision and ground floor execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, interpersonal, and organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent knowledge of Dutch (French as an additional language is a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What&#39;s in it for you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An opportunity to contribute to one of the fastest-growing companies, where you’ll have the chance to create a global impact while being a part of a&amp;nbsp; thriving multinational environment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Daily catered lunches incl. vegetarian options, breakfast, snacks and soft drinks available in our office on daily basis&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commute expenses: Flexport will cover&amp;nbsp; home-office commuting costs for employees living outside of Amsterdam&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 working days as vacation days based on full time employment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health insurance: Flexport offers a collective health insurance plan including a basic package and any available additional packages. Your monthly premium is fully paid by Flexport.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A defined pension contribution scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Equity program: every team member becomes a shareholder, aligning our success with yours. As a private company in a multi-trillion dollar industry, you have a direct stake in our collective growth and success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Assistance Program through Aetna Resources for Living: Flexport provides an employer-sponsored program at no cost to you and your household members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Parental leave benefit: Flexport is here to support you and your families in one of the most important times in life – the birth of a child! Our parental leave program allows both mothers and partners to take time off from work for pregnancy, childbirth, and to bond with your new child.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;1704749847.557549&quot; class=&quot;c-virtual_list__item&quot; data-qa=&quot;virtual-list-item&quot; data-item-key=&quot;1704749847.557549&quot;&gt;
